title: For Sale:  SKS
postcontent:
GET IT BEFORE THE BAN TAKES PLACE! Rare chinese SKS with adjustable stock, scope mount, and bayonet (not pictured).

ALL chinese SKS's are supposed to be marked with chinese symbols & is supposed to have a triangle with a # inside it. This particular SKS is a very rare gun bc there are no chinese symbols or the triangle on the frame. It is only marked "SKS7.62X38CHINA" and also has the serial#. This SKS is a chinese model from the Vietnam War. It was made by the chinese and supplied to the Vietnamese bc their weapon producing factories were bombed and they couldn't manufacture them. There aren't many of these known to exist out there and they're all in private collections bc they're rare. Do some research and you'll see. This isn't your run of the mill SKS. 
http://wiki.answers.com/Q/Identifying_sks_rifle_manufacturer_by_serial_number
http://www.yooperj.com/SKS-24.htm
My grandfather killed a lot of people in the war and this is one of the guns he brought back with him to the states. I had to put the aftermarket stock on (so I could shoot it and make sure it functioned properly, which it does flawlessly) bc the original furniture was damaged during the war. Only asking $1,000 only due to the rarity. It has been appraised for more and would be worth alot more if you could find the stock furniture in good condition. 

also have 20 round mags and 7.62x39 ammo (Brown Bear & Tulammo)

title: For Sale:  Response the messege to ar buyers
postcontent: Everyone is entitled to their own opinion. It funny how all of it looks. I'm not the only one that sees it this way. You could buy an ar a while back for 700 yes. Then its funny somebody mention GUNBAN! Then all of a sudden prices sky rocket over night. The people who all jumped on board we need to ban together and let the people know where we stand. They don't like the way the govt is acting towards the people. Well when they didn't seem to have an issue tripling their prices over night, to use someone's fear for there profit. So I can understand the frustration everyone is having. I can still find ar's being sold at there actual value and not what someone is dreaming about. Sorry nothing going on makes them more rare or more valuable. The media mentioned a possible ban and everybody knew people would flood the stores to buy them. So they knew they could make a killer profit off the media BS. Doesn't matter how you slice it, you can not justify how a 700 rifle is now 2000. I have found multiple colt 6920le on here for 2500 to 3000. Well if you know were to look you can still find people who are not trying to ream others for their benefit. Sorry if I offended anyone. There are still good deals out there if you can find honest people. It goes along with gas prices. They talk about a possible shortage what happens. Prices go up and everybody buys as much as they can. Guess what happens in a couple weeks. Prices come back down. Its sad to say when we need to stick together, others see a prime opportunity to take advantage of others.
